# Album Format Examples

## Your Requested Format
**Pattern**: `%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s`

## How It Works in Different Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Full Album with Metadata
**Source**: YouTube Music album with complete metadata
**Result**:
```
Pink Floyd-The Wall/
├── Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall (Part 1).mp3
├── Pink Floyd-The Happiest Days of Our Lives.mp3
├── Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall (Part 2).mp3
└── Pink Floyd-Mother.mp3
```

### Scenario 2: Compilation Album
**Source**: "Now That's What I Call Music" type playlist
**Result**:
```
Various Artists-Now 50/
├── Taylor Swift-Anti-Hero.mp3
├── Harry Styles-As It Was.mp3
├── Dua Lipa-Levitating.mp3
└── The Weeknd-Blinding Lights.mp3
```

### Scenario 3: YouTube Playlist as Album
**Source**: User-created playlist "My Favorite Rock Songs"
**Result**:
```
Various Artists-My Favorite Rock Songs/
├── Queen-Bohemian Rhapsody.mp3
├── Led Zeppelin-Stairway to Heaven.mp3
├── The Beatles-Hey Jude.mp3
└── Pink Floyd-Comfortably Numb.mp3
```

### Scenario 4: Single Videos (No Album Info)
**Source**: Individual music videos
**Result**:
```
Queen-Unknown Album/
└── Queen-Bohemian Rhapsody.mp3

Led Zeppelin-Unknown Album/
└── Led Zeppelin-Stairway to Heaven.mp3
```

### Scenario 5: Channel Upload (No Artist Metadata)
**Source**: Music uploaded by a channel without proper metadata
**Result**:
```
MusicChannelName-Unknown Album/
├── MusicChannelName-Song Title 1.mp3
├── MusicChannelName-Song Title 2.mp3
└── MusicChannelName-Song Title 3.mp3
```

## Metadata Priority Explanation

### Album Artist Priority:
1. `%(album_artist)s` - Official album artist metadata
2. `%(artist)s` - Track artist metadata  
3. `%(uploader)s` - YouTube channel name

### Album Name Priority:
1. `%(album)s` - Official album metadata
2. `%(playlist)s` - YouTube playlist name
3. `"Unknown Album"` - Default fallback

### Track Artist Priority:
1. `%(artist)s` - Track artist metadata
2. `%(uploader)s` - YouTube channel name

### Track Name Priority:
1. `%(track)s` - Official track metadata
2. `%(title)s` - YouTube video title

## Benefits of This Format

### ✅ Proper Organization
- Albums are grouped by album artist and album name
- Easy to browse music collection
- Consistent directory structure

### ✅ Handles Edge Cases
- Works with incomplete metadata
- Graceful fallbacks for missing information
- Supports both albums and playlists

### ✅ Prevents Conflicts
- Unique directory names with artist-album combination
- Track files include artist to prevent overwrites
- Works with compilation albums

### ✅ Music Player Friendly
- Most music players can parse this structure
- Easy to import into music libraries
- Maintains artist and album relationships

## Usage in Web Interface

1. **Select "Audio only"** checkbox
2. **Choose "Album Artist-Album/Track Artist-Track.mp3 (Albums)"** from dropdown
3. **Download your music** - it will automatically organize using this format

## Custom Variations

If you want to modify the format, you can use "Custom" and try these variations:

### With Track Numbers
```
%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(track_number|00)02d-%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s
```
**Result**: `Pink Floyd-The Wall/01-Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall.mp3`

### With Year
```
%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s (%(release_year|%(upload_date>%Y)|Unknown)s)/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s
```
**Result**: `Pink Floyd-The Wall (1979)/Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall.mp3`

### Spaces Instead of Dashes
```
%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s - %(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s - %(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s
```
**Result**: `Pink Floyd - The Wall/Pink Floyd - Another Brick in the Wall.mp3`

Your requested format strikes the perfect balance between organization, compatibility, and handling edge cases!
