# Audio MP3 File Naming Options for yt-dlp

## Current Default Format
**Current**: `%(uploader)s/%(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `PewDiePie/Amazing Video Title.mp3`

## Available yt-dlp Template Variables

### Basic Information
- `%(title)s` - Video title
- `%(uploader)s` - Channel/uploader name
- `%(uploader_id)s` - Channel ID
- `%(id)s` - Video ID
- `%(ext)s` - File extension (mp3 for audio)

### Dates & Time
- `%(upload_date)s` - Upload date (YYYYMMDD)
- `%(release_date)s` - Release date (YYYYMMDD)
- `%(timestamp)s` - Unix timestamp
- `%(epoch)s` - Unix epoch time

### Duration & Quality
- `%(duration)s` - Duration in seconds
- `%(duration_string)s` - Duration as HH:MM:SS
- `%(abr)s` - Audio bitrate
- `%(asr)s` - Audio sample rate

### Playlist Information
- `%(playlist)s` - Playlist name
- `%(playlist_title)s` - Playlist title
- `%(playlist_id)s` - Playlist ID
- `%(playlist_index)s` - Position in playlist
- `%(playlist_count)s` - Total items in playlist

### Advanced
- `%(artist)s` - Artist name (if available)
- `%(album)s` - Album name (if available)
- `%(track)s` - Track name (if available)
- `%(track_number)s` - Track number (if available)
- `%(genre)s` - Genre (if available)

## Popular Naming Patterns

### 1. Simple Title Only
**Format**: `%(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Minimal, clean filenames

### 2. Artist - Title (Music-like)
**Format**: `%(uploader)s - %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `PewDiePie - Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Music collection organization

### 3. Date-based Organization
**Format**: `%(upload_date)s - %(uploader)s - %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `20231215 - PewDiePie - Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Chronological organization

### 4. Channel Folders with Clean Names
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/%(title)s.%(ext)s` (Current default)
**Example**: `PewDiePie/Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Organized by channel, clean titles

### 5. Channel Folders with IDs
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/%(title)s [%(id)s].%(ext)s`
**Example**: `PewDiePie/Amazing Video Title [dQw4w9WgXcQ].mp3`
**Use case**: Prevent duplicates, easy identification

### 6. Playlist Organization
**Format**: `%(playlist)s/%(playlist_index)02d - %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `My Favorite Songs/01 - Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Maintain playlist order

### 7. Album Artist-Album/Track Artist-Track Format (Recommended for Albums)
**Format**: `%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `Pink Floyd-The Wall/Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall.mp3`
**Use case**: Proper album organization with artist separation
**Note**: This is the format you specifically requested

### 8. Music Album Style (Traditional)
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/%(album|Unknown Album)s/%(track_number|00)02d - %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `Artist Name/Album Name/01 - Song Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Traditional music collection with album organization

### 9. Podcast Style
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/%(upload_date)s - %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `Joe Rogan Experience/20231215 - Amazing Episode Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Podcast episodes with dates

### 10. Duration-based
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/[%(duration_string)s] %(title)s.%(ext)s`
**Example**: `PewDiePie/[12:34] Amazing Video Title.mp3`
**Use case**: Quick duration reference

### 11. Quality-based
**Format**: `%(uploader)s/%(title)s [%(abr)skbps].%(ext)s`
**Example**: `PewDiePie/Amazing Video Title [128kbps].mp3`
**Use case**: Audio quality reference

## Special Characters & Sanitization

yt-dlp automatically handles special characters in filenames:
- Replaces invalid characters with safe alternatives
- Removes or replaces emojis
- Handles Unicode characters appropriately
- Truncates overly long filenames

## Advanced Formatting

### Conditional Fields
Use `%(field|default)s` for fallback values:
- `%(artist|%(uploader)s)s` - Use artist if available, otherwise uploader
- `%(album|Unknown Album)s` - Use album if available, otherwise "Unknown Album"

### Numeric Formatting
- `%(playlist_index)02d` - Zero-padded 2-digit number (01, 02, 03...)
- `%(track_number)03d` - Zero-padded 3-digit number (001, 002, 003...)

### Date Formatting
- `%(upload_date>%Y-%m-%d)s` - Format as YYYY-MM-DD
- `%(upload_date>%B %Y)s` - Format as "December 2023"

## Configuration in Web Interface

The web interface allows you to specify custom yt-dlp arguments including output templates:

1. **Custom yt-dlp arguments field**: `--output "%(uploader)s - %(title)s.%(ext)s"`
2. **Audio extraction**: Check "Audio only" checkbox
3. **Format**: Automatically set to MP3 for audio extraction

## Your Requested Album Format - Detailed Explanation

### Album Artist-Album/Track Artist-Track Format
**Full Pattern**:
```
%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s
```

**How it works**:
1. **Album Artist**: Uses `album_artist` if available, falls back to `artist`, then to `uploader` (channel name)
2. **Album Name**: Uses `album` if available, falls back to `playlist` name, then to "Unknown Album"
3. **Track Artist**: Uses `artist` if available, falls back to `uploader` (channel name)
4. **Track Name**: Uses `track` if available, falls back to `title` (video title)

**Examples**:
- **Full metadata**: `Pink Floyd-The Wall/Pink Floyd-Another Brick in the Wall.mp3`
- **Playlist**: `Various Artists-My Playlist/Artist Name-Song Title.mp3`
- **Single video**: `Channel Name-Unknown Album/Channel Name-Video Title.mp3`

**Benefits**:
- ✅ Proper album organization
- ✅ Handles compilation albums (different track artists)
- ✅ Works with playlists as albums
- ✅ Graceful fallbacks when metadata is missing
- ✅ Consistent naming structure

## Recommended Patterns by Use Case

### Music Collection (Your Format)
```
%(album_artist|%(artist|%(uploader)s)s)s-%(album|%(playlist|Unknown Album)s)s/%(artist|%(uploader)s)s-%(track|%(title)s)s.%(ext)s
```

### Traditional Music Collection
```
%(artist|%(uploader)s)s/%(album|Singles)s/%(track_number|00)02d - %(title)s.%(ext)s
```

### Podcast Archive
```
%(uploader)s/%(upload_date>%Y)s/%(upload_date>%m-%d)s - %(title)s.%(ext)s
```

### Educational Content
```
%(uploader)s/%(playlist|Misc)s/%(playlist_index|000)03d - %(title)s.%(ext)s
```

### General Archive
```
%(uploader)s/%(upload_date>%Y-%m-%d)s - %(title)s [%(id)s].%(ext)s
```

## Implementation Notes

- All patterns work with the current yt-dlp web interface
- Files are automatically saved to `/mnt/storage/media/downloads/audio/`
- Invalid characters are automatically sanitized
- Long filenames are automatically truncated
- Duplicate filenames are handled automatically

## Testing Patterns

You can test different naming patterns by:
1. Using the "Custom yt-dlp arguments" field in the web interface
2. Adding `--output "YOUR_PATTERN_HERE"` to test different formats
3. Downloading a test video to see the result

Example test command:
```
--extract-audio --audio-format mp3 --output "%(uploader)s - %(title)s [%(duration_string)s].%(ext)s"
```
